@node Introduction
"LogoEnhancer.rexx"  is an ARexx-Macro for Simon Edward's 'Image Engineer',
the  shareware image processing application, which can for example be found
on Aminet in the gfx/edit-drawer.
This script modifies an existing logo or any graphical object by creating a
pseudo-3D-bevel  or  neon-effect (see the example picture 'Test.jpg', which
comes with this distribution).

Please note:
1.This macro does not itself create a logo, it merely 'enhances' it, so you
  have to have it drawn with another program (for example Personal-Paint,
  Deluxe-Paint, ArtEffect etc...).
2.Please  make sure that the background of the logo-to-be-modified is plain
  black, also leave a little space around the object, otherwise it might be
 'cut' after the operation.
3.For  the  neon-effect  the  object  is best plain white, the bevel-effect
  looks best with a colourmapped image (again look at 'Test.jpg' ;-)).
@endnode

@node Installation
Simply  copy the file 'LogoEnhancer.rexx' into the 'IE:ARexx/'-drawer.  The
next  time  you  load  Image Engineer and open the ARexx-window, you should
find the item 'LogoEnhancer' in it, to run it, click 'Execute'.
@endnode

@node Usage
To  run  'LogoEnhancer.rexx'  you  will  already  have  to  have  a logo or
graphical  object  created  (read  'Introduction'),  so  load  it, click on
'LogoEnhancer' in the ARexx-window, then 'Execute' and the main window will
pop up:

-'Method' chooses the effect to apply on the logo, e.g.'Bevel' or 'Neon'.
-'Size' chooses  the 'thickness' of the bevel or the scale of the 'corona',
 from 3 (small), 5 (middle) to 7 (large).
-'Contrast-Adjustment'  only applies to the bevel-method, lower values mean
 higher contrast  (darker edges), higher values (highest is 50) mean  lower
 contrast.
-The 'Sharpen'-Checkbox also only effects the bevel-method, using it  gives
 sharper (crisper) images, but should only be used on 'anti-aliased' logos,
 as otherwise it could create ugly square-effects on the finished picture.
-The  'Color'-cycle-gadget is only used for the  neon-method, it  determins
 the color of the corona to be created around the object. Please note:  The
 colors  only  apply  to  plain  white objects,  so if your logo is already
 colored, you  should  best  choose  'As it is', as otherwise the color you
 choose doesn't necessarily translate into the real corona-color.

@endnode

